---
/* ============================================================================
   Homepage
   ============================================================================
   Homepage architecture (replaces the previous eight-section frame).
   Section order is the IA, not decoration:

     Hero          — a tall (clamped, not full 100svh) opening, navy in both
                     themes. An oversized headline + positioning + the one-person
                     differentiator + two CTAs on the left, a crossfading
                     showcase of real client sites on the right (at lg), over a
                     domain-warped WebGL flow, with the client-name marquee
                     riding a thin strip at its base. Studio wordmark lives in the
                     header, not here. (The old separate proof band was folded in
                     here: its differentiator line became hero copy and its
                     marquee moved to the hero floor.)
     Selected Work — three featured case studies, asymmetric (one large + two
                     medium). Real client names, real outcomes, real links into
                     /work/{slug} for the long form.
     Process Band  — single band that combines the four-step process and the
                     inquiry CTA. Closes the page with one strong block instead
                     of three stacked sections.

   The Footer is rendered by BaseLayout, immediately under the Process Band.

   Services, PhotoStrip, and Testimonials are no longer separate homepage
   sections; each was re-homed where it belongs:
     - Services        → /services and /about already carry the offering copy.
     - PhotoStrip      → /photography is the dedicated photography surface; the
                         homepage carries the work via the hero showcase, not a
                         photo tile strip.
     - Testimonials    → embedded inside individual case study pages, and the
                         /about carousel, where the quote has earned context.

   Architecture decision documented in PRODUCT.md and CLAUDE.md — refresh those
   if the section frame ever needs to shift.
   ============================================================================ */

import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Hero from '../components/Hero.astro';
import SelectedWork from '../components/SelectedWork.astro';
import ProcessBand from '../components/ProcessBand.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Nixon Creative Studio | Strategy-led design and photography">
  <Hero />
  <SelectedWork />
  <ProcessBand />
</BaseLayout>
